      <title>Short URL in your GWT project</title>
      <link>https://blog.wlsc.de/2016/04/21/short-url-in-your-gwt-project/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 21 Apr 2016 16:10:17 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.wlsc.de/2016/04/21/short-url-in-your-gwt-project/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&#34;size-medium wp-image-88 aligncenter&#34; src=&#34;https://blog.wlsc.de/images/2016/04/pgtqyluoyhr1swo4wrmn-300x115.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;url&#34; width=&#34;300&#34; height=&#34;115&#34; srcset=&#34;https://blog.wlsc.de/images/2016/04/pgtqyluoyhr1swo4wrmn-300x115.jpg 300w, https://blog.wlsc.de/images/2016/04/pgtqyluoyhr1swo4wrmn-768x295.jpg 768w, https://blog.wlsc.de/images/2016/04/pgtqyluoyhr1swo4wrmn-1024x393.jpg 1024w&#34; sizes=&#34;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are strugling with a long URL in the GWT project, you are at the right place! There is a small trick, which allows URL to be shorter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&#34;theme:eclipse lang:xhtml decode:true&#34;&gt;https://domain.com/tomcat_context_path/project_name/your_index.html&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&#34;theme:eclipse lang:xhtml decode:true &#34;&gt;https://domain.com/tomcat_context_path/&lt;/pre&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Launching GWT app in SuperDevMode on local Tomcat server</title>
      <link>https://blog.wlsc.de/2015/10/03/launching-gwt-app-in-superdevmode-on-local-tomcat-server/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 03 Oct 2015 22:32:57 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.wlsc.de/2015/10/03/launching-gwt-app-in-superdevmode-on-local-tomcat-server/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&#34;size-full wp-image-15 aligncenter&#34; src=&#34;https://blog.wlsc.de/images/2015/10/navLogoBig.png&#34; alt=&#34;GWT project logo&#34; width=&#34;150&#34; height=&#34;158&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This article is dedicated to all people who are still developing on internal Jetty server and do not know how to run their product on &lt;a href=&#34;http://tomcat.apache.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Apache Tomcat server&lt;/a&gt;. This guide is valid for &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.eclipse.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Eclipse IDE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; (Currently: v4.5 MARS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First of all, if you are not familiar with &lt;strong&gt;SuperDevMode&lt;/strong&gt; and its prerequisites, please, check the official docs at &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.gwtproject.org/articles/superdevmode.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.gwtproject.org&#34;&gt;http://www.gwtproject.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
